  <Name>k__BackingField: II Peter
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 2pe
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting the Faithful'
      title: Greeting the Faithful
      number: 1
      content: 'Simon Peter, a bondservant and apostle of Jesus Christ,To those who
        have obtained like precious faith with us by the righteousness of our God
        and Savior Jesus Christ:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Grace and peace be multiplied to you in the knowledge of God and
        of Jesus our Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'as His divine power has given to us all things that pertain to life
        and godliness, through the knowledge of Him who called us by glory and virtue, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Fruitful Growth in the Faith'
      title: Fruitful Growth in the Faith
      number: 4
      content: by which have been given to us exceedingly great and precious promises,
        that through these you may be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped
        the corruption that  is in the world through lust.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But also for this very reason, giving all diligence, add to your
        faith virtue, to virtue knowledge, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'to knowledge self-control, to self-control perseverance, to perseverance
        godliness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'to godliness brotherly kindness, and to brotherly kindness love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For if these things are yours and abound, you will be neither barren
        nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For he who lacks these things is shortsighted, even to blindness,
        and has forgotten that he was cleansed from his old sins.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore, brethren, be even more diligent to make your call and
        election sure, for if you do these things you will never stumble; '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Peter\u2019s Approaching Death"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Approaching Death"
      number: 11
      content: for so an entrance will be supplied to you abundantly into the everlasting
        kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For this reason I will not be negligent to remind you always of these
        things, though you know and are established in the present truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yes, I think it is right, as long as I am in this tent, to stir you
        up by reminding you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'knowing that shortly I must put off my tent, just as our Lord Jesus
        Christ showed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Trustworthy Prophetic Word'
      title: The Trustworthy Prophetic Word
      number: 15
      content: Moreover I will be careful to ensure that you always have a reminder
        of these things after my decease.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For we did not follow cunningly devised fables when we made known
        to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but were eyewitnesses
        of His majesty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For He received from God the Father honor and glory when such a voice
        came to Him from the Excellent Glory: \u201CThis is My beloved Son, in whom
        I am well pleased.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And we heard this voice which came from heaven when we were with Him
        on the holy mountain.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And so we have the prophetic word confirmed, which you do well to
        heed as a light that shines in a dark place, until the day dawns and the
        morning star rises in your hearts; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'knowing this first, that no prophecy of Scripture is of any private
        interpretation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: for prophecy never came by the will of man, but holy men of God spoke
        as  they  were moved by the Holy Spirit.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Destructive Doctrines'
      title: Destructive Doctrines
      number: 1
      content: 'But there were also false prophets among the people, even as there
        will be false teachers among you, who will secretly bring in destructive
        heresies, even denying the Lord who bought them, and bring on themselves
        swift destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And many will follow their destructive ways, because of whom the
        way of truth will be blasphemed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Doom of False Teachers'
      title: Doom of False Teachers
      number: 3
      content: By covetousness they will exploit you with deceptive words; for a
        long time their judgment has not been idle, and their destruction does not
        slumber.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For if God did not spare the angels who sinned, but cast them down
        to hell and delivered them into chains of darkness, to be reserved for judgment; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and did not spare the ancient world, but saved Noah, one  of eight
        people, a preacher of righteousness, bringing in the flood on the world of
        the ungodly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and turning the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah into ashes, condemned
        them to destruction, making them an example to those who afterward would
        live ungodly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and delivered righteous Lot, who  was oppressed by the filthy conduct
        of the wicked '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "(for that righteous man, dwelling among them, tormented his righteous
        soul from day to day by seeing and hearing their lawless deeds)\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then  the Lord knows how to deliver the godly out of temptations
        and to reserve the unjust under punishment for the day of judgment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and especially those who walk according to the flesh in the lust
        of uncleanness and despise authority. They  are presumptuous, self-willed.
        They are not afraid to speak evil of dignitaries, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Depravity of False Teachers'
      title: Depravity of False Teachers
      number: 11
      content: whereas angels, who are greater in power and might, do not bring a
        reviling accusation against them before the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But these, like natural brute beasts made to be caught and destroyed,
        speak evil of the things they do not understand, and will utterly perish
        in their own corruption, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and will receive the wages of unrighteousness, as those who count
        it pleasure to carouse in the daytime. They  are spots and blemishes, carousing
        in their own deceptions while they feast with you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'having eyes full of adultery and that cannot cease from sin, enticing
        unstable souls. They have a heart trained in covetous practices, and  are
        accursed children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They have forsaken the right way and gone astray, following the way
        of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "but he was rebuked for his iniquity: a dumb donkey speaking with
        a man\u2019s voice restrained the madness of the prophet."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Deceptions of False Teachers'
      title: Deceptions of False Teachers
      number: 17
      content: These are wells without water, clouds carried by a tempest, for whom
        is reserved the blackness of darkness forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For when they speak great swelling words of emptiness, they allure
        through the lusts of the flesh, through lewdness, the ones who have actually
        escaped from those who live in error. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'While they promise them liberty, they themselves are slaves of corruption;
        for by whom a person is overcome, by him also he is brought into bondage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For if, after they have escaped the pollutions of the world through
        the knowledge of the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, they are again entangled
        in them and overcome, the latter end is worse for them than the beginning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For it would have been better for them not to have known the way
        of righteousness, than having known it, to turn from the holy commandment
        delivered to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But it has happened to them according to the true proverb: \u201CA
        dog returns to his own vomit,\u201D and, \u201Ca sow, having washed, to her
        wallowing in the mire.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Promise Is Not Slack"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise Is Not Slack"
      number: 1
      content: 'Beloved, I now write to you this second epistle (in both  of which
        I stir up your pure minds by way of reminder), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that you may be mindful of the words which were spoken before by
        the holy prophets, and of the commandment of us, the apostles of the Lord
        and Savior, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'knowing this first: that scoffers will come in the last days, walking
        according to their own lusts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and saying, \u201CWhere is the promise of His coming? For since the
        fathers fell asleep, all things continue as they  were from the beginning
        of creation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For this they willfully forget: that by the word of God the heavens
        were of old, and the earth standing out of water and in the water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'by which the world that then existed perished, being flooded with
        water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But the heavens and the earth which are now preserved by the same
        word, are reserved for fire until the day of judgment and perdition of ungodly
        men.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But, beloved, do not forget this one thing, that with the Lord one
        day is as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Day of the Lord'
      title: The Day of the Lord
      number: 9
      content: The Lord is not slack concerning His promise, as some count slackness,
        but is longsuffering toward us, not willing that any should perish but that
        all should come to repentance.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night, in which
        the heavens will pass away with a great noise, and the elements will melt
        with fervent heat; both the earth and the works that are in it will be burned
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, since all these things will be dissolved, what manner
        of  persons ought you to be in holy conduct and godliness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'looking for and hastening the coming of the day of God, because of
        which the heavens will be dissolved, being on fire, and the elements will
        melt with fervent heat? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Be Steadfast'
      title: Be Steadfast
      number: 13
      content: Nevertheless we, according to His promise, look for new heavens and
        a new earth in which righteousness dwells.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, beloved, looking forward to these things, be diligent
        to be found by Him in peace, without spot and blameless; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and consider that  the longsuffering of our Lord is salvation\u2014as
        also our beloved brother Paul, according to the wisdom given to him, has
        written to you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: as also in all his epistles, speaking in them of these things, in
        which are some things hard to understand, which untaught and unstable people
        twist to their own destruction, as they  do also the rest of the Scriptures.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You therefore, beloved, since you know this beforehand, beware lest
        you also fall from your own steadfastness, being led away with the error
        of the wicked; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: but grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.To
        Him be the glory both now and forever. Amen.
      comments: []
